<subSubSection id="171837145400CBEA92A3AC3320EA06E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1D5FBD4F5E64B24928E41DD0B8B3167A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="699235611CDEE6D6F09235AB5686FB1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Head circular frontally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1BF2F0C72F6B48649F2AD9D60D367A02" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2C</figureCitation>
); lower face with dense and long setation, setae adpressed and lanceolate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E92FE4B483DE1B28374810B509CF31FC" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2D</figureCitation>
); scape of antenna shorter, only 5.56
<normalizedToken id="3AAC1567CDC4ADB2CF56466A70562F20" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; F2-F4 more than 2.5
<normalizedToken id="791AC767471A6E0C880CE708FEDBC846" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2A144B881D4FAF522C0DB88C8A5C2EC4" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2E</figureCitation>
); mesoscutellum only 1.26
<normalizedToken id="EBC0F875A48A6EF3B2C851331E72B181" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2334ECA8D4294BF1026C330BE731B7DD" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2B</figureCitation>
); propodeum irregularly longitudinally striate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DE80C2C767283E373784F3860919E2F8" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2F</figureCitation>
); metatarsomere 4 (mtar4) with elongated unpaired spur-like seta, seta about as long as length of mtar4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7D11EFF03BB7168A434349CBD0FEEEA9" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2J</figureCitation>
); fore wing with five brown maculae, pear-like macula ventrad to parastigma, around stigmal vein and three brown maculae on tip of wing; stigma elongated, broadening in posterior half with tapering end (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BB76CDCCBA862DDC66FB56B528034FC9" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2H</figureCitation>
); metasoma with tip of hypopygium reaching more than 0.75
<normalizedToken id="28A2ADAF3A40E26B3F30B3C07501354A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
of length of gaster (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7F5A6FFD4B46874897ACD2EEA91AA8E5" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2I</figureCitation>
); OI 1.14.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A9571D9190DA02EF3C143382178E988A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph id="12411DD4AD7CA082A6E9C335200E6853" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F45B413048D41122DB17AC834302C08" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="149D4D14262CF0ED7D2ABD85AA7BCD2F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Female. 
<emphasis id="92C8B0514EB343C3543EA2D6AF68D4EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Holotype</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Body length excluding ovipositor 2.47 mm; length of ovipositor 0.89 mm (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F66D7E3A2ABEB6491EDC20BBFDF482F6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2A, B</figureCitation>
). Vertex except small area between lateral ocellus to upper eye margin and between median ocellus and scrobes, upper face between scrobes and inner eye margin, lower face laterally, posterior part of mesoscutal midlobe, posterior half to third of mesoscutellum, axilla, callus posterior to spiracle, anterior 0.66
<normalizedToken id="DB7F5CFAA392D15F35366812C2019387" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
of propodeum, and metapleuron blue violet. Supraclypeal area, clypeus, temple, pronotal collar, lateral lobe of mesoscutum, lower mesepisternum, fore coxa and femur, hind coxa and metasomal tergites laterally with violet tint. Fore wing transparent except brown pear-like macula under parastigma, broad brown macula surrounding stigmal vein and three brown maculae on tip of wing with anterior one the largest, posterior one smaller.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C773640D5E645A1202483E58C8A8E628" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="3FE1350FA4B84965CCB870F8B63A37C9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="5792882E3ABF8230E249693B5725B095" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Vertex and face reticulate. Head appearing circular from frontal view, vertex convex and median ocellus relatively high above upper eye margin; 1.14
<normalizedToken id="08D67FD335128724B768BA969D3A34AB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as high (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2DE69051AF73D076B19FE15403E06B5D" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2C</figureCitation>
); 1.69
<normalizedToken id="26450E2C4B99571EDFE4A4C96AB1FD2E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long; 1.35
<normalizedToken id="76EBEF0DD33D484EDFCB59224CDBF0DD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as mesonotum at its widest part in dorsal view. Temple short, converging, 0.23
<normalizedToken id="7ECB9C17FF7313F53138649A20720AC3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as eye (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6ED8A4EA208661CD72C9707FA58CAE78" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2B</figureCitation>
). Eyes separated by 1.02
<normalizedToken id="0C520C2653EAAD99DC1D34AFD7A24B97" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their own height; eye 1.34
<normalizedToken id="4B8678A1CBD93C13C684040EDC5885F4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as long. Face setae adpressed; very dense on lower face so that clypeus surface not clearly visible (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CD3E578C61EA74C2F3310317854C2287" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2D</figureCitation>
); upper face with setae only along eye (one incomplete row) and scrobes (in about three rows) and few additional setae on vertex. Scrobes only slightly longer than half length of scape. Malar space 0.45
<normalizedToken id="927AB84323C0046BC91C8B5C7BE85CD1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as breadth of oral fossa and 0.42
<normalizedToken id="1B0BB95A07E648B9C91056AEC0623DF1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as eye height. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="701302928C68584EF9B35A03E0951245" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2E</figureCitation>
) with scape 5.56
<normalizedToken id="AA131CE4300E864B688A4BB3863ADF4B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
and pedicel 1.56
<normalizedToken id="387712ED3F2DCFB4F76BBFAF0F27EB9F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, the former slightly curved in lateral view and reaching above dorsal margin of posterior ocellus. Combined length of pedicel and flagellum 1.87
<normalizedToken id="0EDB6017941838A62E0677ACCD5817B0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as breadth of head. Anellus transverse. Relative length/breadth (ratio) of funiculars as follows: F1 22.5/10 (2.25), F2 24/9.5 (2.53), F3 25/9.5 (2.63), F4 24/9.5 (2.53), F5 22.5/9.5 (2.37), F6 21/9.5 (2.21), F7 19/11.5 (1.65). Clava with relative length/breadth (ratio) 30.5/15 (2.03). POL 1.35
<normalizedToken id="68D7E34C16786AA4E4021096A464CEE6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OOL, OOL 2.18
<normalizedToken id="A0EB09DB718182E9659D982767950347" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as POD. Left mandible with three teeth, right mandible denticulation hidden under left mandible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D0D7426F5B7989C5E2ADF53AB25CC57" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="3EE3B822A2EBC7D747FC31419981A55F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="01FA0AA9DC2BCABD278A00014919E5C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Mesosoma 2.13
<normalizedToken id="1A9F5F961C2A4B2441F692CAEF6F720C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A676AC77A6F9F228E6823E001D7723F2" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2B</figureCitation>
). Pronotum 0.85
<normalizedToken id="9C86CFBC04E9B7E36D2745E2BA9BDB3E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as mesoscutum. Pronotal collar about 3.09
<normalizedToken id="90143AA7B54358B9593BE121B08E4027" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long, with two incomplete but well raised transverse striae medially and with few additional incomplete lower striae laterally and lateromedially. Mesoscutellum 1.26
<normalizedToken id="A971BBA3479A0F8D39650CD646963982" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, without frenal area, and with two rows of (probably) three setae submedially. Propodeum 2.20
<normalizedToken id="CDCC5960980FF59EFAF5765AFA30DBA6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="92C9A930928F73E27B762D8B341628F8" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2F</figureCitation>
). Area between spiracles irregularly longitudinally striate; with few long white setae medially. Metacoxa 2.00
<normalizedToken id="AACDE2D6AF6ECE199FE62F10CDC06C33" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, with long setation dorsally and ventrally; metafemur 4.50
<normalizedToken id="562669A58570C7608F1F1592371361E6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; metatibia 8.15
<normalizedToken id="78712230DDC895571EA80C00B952C4A4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; metatarsus relatively short, only 0.68
<normalizedToken id="FAC8710E31CF204F147471A3363E08E2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as metatibia. Metatarsomere 4 (mtar4) bearing elongated unpaired spur-like seta, seta about as long as length of mtar4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="26499F42700F064C853989F9A2CB82E0" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2J</figureCitation>
). Fore wing 2.63
<normalizedToken id="EACF948A4EBB1D731A893132DCDBEEF6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, slightly infumate ventral to parastigma and clear brown macula surrounding stigmal vein and three brown maculae on tip of wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="877A4017468A7BCFD2E6E5CD0EDA551B" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2H</figureCitation>
); basal setal line complete, with several setae dorsally; mediocubital setal line with at least 3 setae dorsally in distal third; marginal vein 0.78
<normalizedToken id="4D24A8498EB8E6C22B9CB8857DEFC3F7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as postmarginal vein and 1.40
<normalizedToken id="E25AB8595954D202CD715986F8F49F41" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as stigmal vein; stigma broadening in posterior half with tapering end, 4.40
<normalizedToken id="77023834E60D17318698E7976661DCB6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; stigmal vein posteriorly and stigma transparent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADEA8EAD111B3C1CC5955A718D20CCC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="13F5D9D79BA7629A4913D183A5EEDBCD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="10BE0EB220EE1AA0B93B82C54977830F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Metasoma 1.17
<normalizedToken id="336C798211FF10655D46DFD59E642156" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as mesosoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B72E471A23038B4F69A9BD367BFF011B" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2A</figureCitation>
). Gaster not compressed laterally and with very shallow alutaceous sculpture; tip of hypopygium reaching more than 0.75
<normalizedToken id="8409ADA777EA3E21557B0DDFBD7FACCF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
of length of gaster. Ovipositor upturned; OI 1.14.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3AD16729555E4630ADF7B4EB831AB01E" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="47D634025619B4E330BDDA9567A83B19" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6FA08D84620873801FF334EAB274178B" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C78B5B9D25BDDE8635884F45638EDE08" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1BF24F4B4BB55C6DEB33944146C5317A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Named after the distinctive brown maculae on fore wings.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A58CCE9D6E2D143A38E65621F1ED620F" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="03AB423BA165D3AA15595A44EBBEDDFA" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="59F78233E151E0CD909977F8B486CF91" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D4AC4F2A4BFC543AC8A3BE70ABFDFD82" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="82829C27381A621A284FA0B119ED1F0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="67AFEC93E594A9C4593CD9AEF1785B80" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Australia: Queensland, Kirrama State forest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9BF3126BC063CA8116C15F04141998E" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="condition of the holotype">
<paragraph id="382A5DDDC9768EB66DC1F38BA4B997F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Condition of the holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21E16A3979C9EB95DA989426754486CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Unfortunately the unique specimen collected, the holotype female, was broken during imaging and several parts are now glued on three separate cards: one triangular card bears left fore and hind wing; a second triangular card with head including right scape, pedicel and annelus, part of mesosoma with right fore and hind wings and forelegs into one piece and mesophragma as a second piece; and a third rectangular card with right flagellum, metasoma, right mid leg, hind legs and posterior part of mesosoma including propodeum.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
